Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, there has been an increase in the number of calls from fraudsters who replace the bank&#39;s phone number.
This is reported by &quot;Kommersant&quot; with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator transmitted information to telecom operators about more than 2.5 thousand numbers from which they called clients of various financial organizations.
