Russian gays with adopted children seek asylum in the United States
A same-sex couple of Russians with two adopted children have applied for asylum in the United States, RIA Novosti reports.
The men reportedly left the Russian Federation for Ukraine, after which they went to the States, where they applied for asylum.
According to the Stimul group, the basis for such actions of the family was &quot;the continuing interest on the part of law enforcement agencies.&quot;
Reportedly, the men do not plan to return to Russia.
Children from the beginning of the school year study at an American school and adapt to new conditions.
We will remind, earlier it was reported about the initiation of a case against employees of the department of social protection of the population of the Maryino district due to the adoption by a same-sex family of two little boys.
At the same time, the HRC stated that raising children by a same-sex couple in itself should not become a reason for initiating a case.
